details:
Case 167 is a 35 year-old female Filipino national who is a Singapore Work Pass holder, and is a family member of Case 178. She had been in the Philippines from 11 February to 17 February. She is warded in an isolation room at NTFGH.

She reported onset of symptoms on 8 March and had sought treatment at Ng Teng Fong General Hospital on 9 March. Subsequent test results confirmed COVID-19 infection on 10 March afternoon.

She is employed as a staff nurse at Ng Teng Fong General Hospital and had been at work prior to hospital admission. She stays at Jurong East Street 21.
